The paper discusses an accelerator architecture for convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision applications. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also focuses on improving performance and energy efficiency, which falls under cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The use of network pruning and ReLU activation also suggests a connection to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
